  "title": "Consulting Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Execute application development deliverables and activities.</li><li>Perform software development related to Identity Access Management and related technology e.g. SailPoint and Java</li><li>Participate in various phases of the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) for IT Projects and to interface with various IT stakeholders such as 3rd party vendor, business analysts and project managers to perform development activities</li><li>Documenting the application technical specifications and database design</li><li>Troubleshooting incidents/defects and resolving technical issues</li><li>Deploy components and applications on windows environment – client and server based</li><li>Work closely with the Application Development team members and Architects to develop code that is aligned to approved design and specifications</li><li>Work closely with the Application Development team and QA teams to ensure any defects highlighted in QA or UAT phases are remediated</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong>:</p><ul><li>6+ years software development experience and can demonstrate strong understanding of SDLC fundamentals</li><li>6+ years experience in <strong>Sailpoint application development</strong> as a <strong>Identity Access Management Solution developer</strong></li><li>Excellent knowledge and understanding of <strong>LDAP </strong>concepts and working experience with at least few of the LDAPs</li><li>Extensive Experience in development/support of workflows, forms and other <strong>SailPoint IDM Component</strong></li><li>Experience working with Application/Web Servers (Tomcat, WebLogic, Websphere) or developing J2EE products</li><li>Experienced with the usage of Software design patterns</li><li>Proficient In the usage of Sailpoint and Java</li><li>Experience in building identity access management solutions and access certifications</li><li>Proficient in the usages of RDBMS – MS SQL Server</li><li>Proficient in REST based APIs using JSON and web services</li></ul>",
